name: RigidbodyBuiltin
description: Represents a Rigidbody component that enables physics simulation for game objects.

instanceFields.label: Owner
instanceFields.description: The MapObject this rigidbody is attached to.

instanceFields.label: Position
instanceFields.description: The position of the Rigidbody in world space. This is the same as the position of the GameObject it is attached to.

instanceFields.label: Rotation
instanceFields.description: The rotation of the Rigidbody in world space. This is the same as the rotation of the GameObject it is attached to.

instanceFields.label: Velocity
instanceFields.description: The velocity of the Rigidbody in world space.

instanceFields.label: AngularVelocity
instanceFields.description: The angular velocity of the Rigidbody in world space.

instanceFields.label: AngularDrag
instanceFields.description: The angular damping of the Rigidbody. This is a multiplier applied to the angular velocity every frame, reducing it over time.

instanceFields.label: Mass
instanceFields.description: The Mass of the Rigidbody

instanceFields.label: UseGravity
instanceFields.description: Whether or not the Rigidbody use gravity.

instanceFields.label: Gravity
instanceFields.description: The force of gravity applied to the Rigidbody. If null, the Rigidbody will use Unity's default gravity settings and will enable gravity. If Vector3 is provided, it will apply that as a custom gravity force using ConstantForce and disable gravity.

instanceFields.label: FreezeXPosition
instanceFields.description: If the x movement axis is frozen

instanceFields.label: FreezeYPosition
instanceFields.description: If the y movement axis is frozen

instanceFields.label: FreezeZPosition
instanceFields.description: If the z movement axis is frozen

instanceFields.label: FreezeXRotation
instanceFields.description: If the x rotation axis is frozen

instanceFields.label: FreezeYRotation
instanceFields.description: If the y rotation axis is frozen

instanceFields.label: FreezeZRotation
instanceFields.description: If the z rotation axis is frozen

instanceFields.label: FreezeAllRotations
instanceFields.description: Freeze all rotations

instanceFields.label: FreezeAllPositions
instanceFields.description: Freeze all positions. This will also freeze all rotations.

instanceFields.label: IsKinematic
instanceFields.description: If the Rigidbody is kinematic. Kinematic bodies are not affected by forces and can only be moved manually.

instanceFields.label: Interpolate
instanceFields.description: Interpolation mode of the Rigidbody. If true, it will interpolate between frames.

instanceFields.label: CenterOfMass
instanceFields.description: The center of mass of the Rigidbody in local space.

instanceFields.label: CollisionDetectionMode
instanceFields.description: The collision detection mode of the Rigidbody. This determines how collisions are detected and resolved.

instanceFields.label: DetectCollisions
instanceFields.description: If the Rigidbody detects collisions. If false, it will not collide with other colliders.

instanceMethods.label: AddForce
instanceMethods.description: Apply a force to the Rigidbody - legacy version, please use optimized if possible.

parameters.name: atPoint
parameters.description: Optional. If provided, applies force at this world position instead of center of mass.

instanceMethods.label: AddForceOptimized
instanceMethods.description: Apply a force to the Rigidbody.

parameters.name: forceMode
parameters.description: The force mode as integer (use ForceModeAcceleration, ForceModeForce, ForceModeImpulse, or ForceModeVelocityChange constants, default: 5).

parameters.name: atPoint
parameters.description: Optional. If provided, applies force at this world position instead of center of mass.

instanceMethods.label: AddTorque
instanceMethods.description: Apply a torque to the Rigidbody - legacy version, please use optimized if possible.

instanceMethods.label: AddTorqueOptimized
instanceMethods.description: Apply a torque to the Rigidbody.

parameters.name: forceMode
parameters.description: The force mode as integer (use ForceModeAcceleration, ForceModeForce, ForceModeImpulse, or ForceModeVelocityChange constants, default: 5).

instanceMethods.label: AddExplosionForce
instanceMethods.description: Apply an explosion force to the Rigidbody.

parameters.name: explosionPosition
parameters.description: The center position of the explosion.

parameters.name: upwardsModifier
parameters.description: Adjustment to the apparent position of the explosion to make it seem to lift objects (default: 0.0).

parameters.name: forceMode
parameters.description: The force mode as integer (use ForceModeAcceleration, ForceModeForce, ForceModeImpulse, or ForceModeVelocityChange constants, default: 5).

instanceMethods.label: Move
instanceMethods.description: Move the Rigidbody to a new position. This will not apply any forces, it will just set the position directly.

instanceMethods.label: MovePosition
instanceMethods.description: Move the Rigidbody to a new position. This will apply forces to move the Rigidbody to the new position.

instanceMethods.label: MoveRotation
instanceMethods.description: Move the Rigidbody to a new rotation. This will apply forces to rotate the Rigidbody to the new rotation.

instanceMethods.label: ResetCenterOfMass
instanceMethods.description: Reset the center of mass of the Rigidbody to the default value (0, 0, 0). This will also reset the inertia tensor.

instanceMethods.label: PublishTransform
instanceMethods.description: Publish the current position and rotation of the Rigidbody to the MapObject. This will update the MapObject's transform to match the Rigidbody's transform.

instanceMethods.label: SweepTest
instanceMethods.description: Checks if the rigidbody would collide with anything, returns a LineCastHitResult object.
